OwnableInvalidOwner(address).details: The owner is not a valid owner account. (eg. `address(0)`)

OwnableUnauthorizedAccount(address).details: The caller account is not authorized to perform an operation.

TaskDecrypted(uint256,address,uint64,uin.details: Event emitted when a task is successfully decrypted

createTask(bytes32,bytes32,bytes32,bytes.details: Creates a new confidential task for the caller.

params.encryptedDueDate: The encrypted due date of the task.
params.encryptedPriority: The encrypted priority of the task (e.g., 1-5).
params.encryptedTitle: The encrypted title of the task.
params.inputProof: The ZK proof for the encrypted inputs.

createTaskWithNumbers(bytes32,bytes32,by.details: Creates a new confidential task with numeric title and ID.

params.encryptedDueDate: The encrypted due date of the task.
params.encryptedNumericId: The encrypted numeric ID for the task.
params.encryptedPriority: The encrypted priority of the task (1-5).
params.encryptedTitle: The encrypted title of the task (as number).
params.inputProof: The ZK proof for the encrypted inputs.

createTaskWithText(bytes32,bytes32,bytes.details: Creates a new confidential task with text title and description.

params.encryptedDescription: The encrypted description of the task (as number).
params.encryptedDueDate: The encrypted due date of the task.
params.encryptedPriority: The encrypted priority of the task (1-5).
params.encryptedTitle: The encrypted title of the task (as number).
params.inputProof: The ZK proof for the encrypted inputs.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

requestSharedTaskDecryptionById(uint256,.details: Requests decryption of a shared task (for recipients) using stable taskId. This allows users to decrypt tasks that were shared with them.

params.originalOwner: The address of the task's original owner

requestTaskDecryptionById(uint256).details: Requests decryption of a specific task for the caller (by stable taskId). This function initiates the decryption process for FHEVM encrypted data.

setFee(uint256).details: Sets a new fee for task creation. Only callable by the owner.

taskDecryptionCallback(uint256,bytes,byt.details: Callback function called by the relayer after decryption. This function receives the decrypted data and can process it.

params.requestId: The ID of the decryption request

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw().details: Withdraws the entire contract balance to the owner's address.

HandlesAlreadySavedForRequestID().notice: Returned if some handles were already saved for corresponding ID.

InvalidKMSSignatures().notice: Returned if the returned KMS signatures are not valid.

NoHandleFoundForRequestID().notice: Returned if there was not handle found for the requested ID.

DecryptionFulfilled(uint256).notice: This event is emitted when requested decryption has been fulfilled.
